{"user_message": {"title": "ADR 0002 — Currency-aware banker's rounding (implemented + green)", "content": "## ADR 0002 — Currency-aware banker's rounding utility\n\n**Status:** Accepted · **Area:** `src/features/ledger/lib` · **Relates to:** ADR 0001\n\n### Context\nADR 0001 canonicalizes USD via a private `roundToCents` that uses `Math.round` = **half-UP**, and ADR 0001 itself flagged sub-cent **upward tie-bias drift** in aggregates (`computeSDE`) as residual risk. There was no reusable, currency-aware rounding primitive (`roundToCents` is hard-coded to 2dp and private).\n\n### Decision\nAdded `src/features/ledger/lib/round.ts`:\n- **`roundMoney(value, currency)`** — pure **round-half-to-even (banker's)** rounding to the currency's minor units. Half-detection uses a `1e-9` epsilon (FP ties like `0.005*100` are never exactly `.5`).\n- **`minorUnits` / `MINOR_UNITS` / `DEFAULT_MINOR_UNITS`** — per-ISO-4217 decimals (USD/EUR=2, JPY/KRW=0, BHD/KWD=3, default 2), case-insensitive.\n- **NaN/Infinity-safe = fail-loud:** non-finite value / non-number / blank currency → `RangeError`, consistent with `amount.ts` rejecting `not-finite`. Canonical representation unchanged (signed 2-decimal `number`) → zero consumer churn.\n\nDoes **not** contradict ADR 0001: `amount.ts`'s half-up at the *input boundary* is harmless (single freshly-parsed magnitude, no tie-bias accumulation); converging it is a scoped follow-up.\n\n### Consequences\n- **+** reusable tested primitive; half-even removes tie-bias for future aggregation/allocation/splits; currency-aware ahead of non-USD; corrupt values fail loud at the arithmetic layer too.\n- **−** two rounding helpers coexist (`roundToCents` half-up, `roundMoney` half-even) until Task 4 converges them; epsilon degrades above `MAX_SAFE_INTEGER` (out of range — $1M per-tx ceiling).\n\n### Task breakdown (8 pts total — 6 delivered, 2 deferred)\n1. `roundMoney` + minor-units table — **3 pts** ✅ implemented\n2. Edge-case unit tests (half-even boundary, negative, zero/-0, 0/3-dp currencies, very large/small, non-finite guards) — **2 pts** ✅ implemented\n3. Barrel export from `features/ledger/index.ts` — **1 pt** ✅ implemented\n4. Converge `roundToCents` → `roundMoney` (half-up→half-even, re-validate 12 boundary tests) — **2 pts** ⏸ follow-up, blocked on first aggregation consumer\n\n### Verification\n```chart\nNew round tests passing: 13\nAmount tests passing: 12\nTotal suite passing: 25\n```\n- `npm test` → **25/25 green** (`tsx` + `node:test`).\n- `tsc --noEmit` clean for the new module; only the pre-existing unrelated `e2e/benchmarks-compare.unit.spec.ts` error remains (already documented in ADR 0001).\n- Files: `src/features/ledger/lib/round.ts`, `…/round.test.ts`, barrel `…/index.ts`, ADR `docs/adr/0002-currency-aware-banker-rounding.md`, shared note `Athena/decision-currency-aware-banker-rounding.md`.\n\n**Implemented — not stopped at a plan.** A delivery agent can pick up Task 4 when an aggregation path first needs rounding.", "content_type": "success", "priority": "normal"}}

